{"TopicId":115675,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Is there any easy way to clean up debris?","CreatedByName":"Xwingace","CreatedById":133896,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-11T23:15:07Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Xwingace","CreatedById":133896,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-11T23:15:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ELots of debris in orbit, I\u0027d like to get rid of it but the only way I can see is selecting each one individually. Is there an easier way?\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-07-26T05:20:37Z\u0022 title=\u002207/26/2015 05:20  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 26, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Xwingace\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Glaran K\u0026#039;erman","CreatedById":146334,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-11T23:24:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAre you talking about from the Tracking Station? Even with a lot of debris it shouldn\u0027t take more than a couple minutes to terminate them all from there.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HoloYolo","CreatedById":138353,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-11T23:33:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EGo to settings and limit debris to 0. No more debris ever again.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Glaran K\u0026#039;erman","CreatedById":146334,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-11T23:37:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kaboom!\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Kaboom!\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EGo to settings and limit debris to 0. No more debris ever again.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESweet, gonna do this right now myself\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HoloYolo","CreatedById":138353,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-11T23:39:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Glaran K\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Glaran K\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ESweet\u0027 date=\u0027 gonna do this right now myself[/quote\u0027]Alrighty\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geschosskopf","CreatedById":69507,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-12T00:04:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xwingace\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Xwingace\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EIs there an easier way?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUse the TAC Self-Destruct mod to not make any debris to being with.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBut if you\u0027re stuck with it already, by far the easiest method is to \u0022Deathstar\u0022 stuff via \u0022this fully operatiounal battle station\u0022 aka the Tracking Station.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://flic.kr/p/vAS6Md\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://farm1.staticflickr.com/452/19428882178_701f19ca1b_z.jpg\u0022 alt=\u002219428882178_701f19ca1b_z.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FancyMouse","CreatedById":142946,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-12T00:36:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EBut what if it\u0027s at the other side of the planet (blocked by Kerbin/Mun/etc.)?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"legoclone09","CreatedById":142607,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-12T17:21:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FancyMouse\u0022 data-cite=\u0022FancyMouse\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EBut what if it\u0027s at the other side of the planet (blocked by Kerbin/Mun/etc.)?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStill works fine. Tracking station can terminate a ten thousand part ship in an orbit 2x as large as Eeloo\u0027s.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xwingace","CreatedById":133896,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-26T05:18:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kaboom!\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Kaboom!\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EGo to settings and limit debris to 0. No more debris ever again.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou are gentleman and a scholar, thank you.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}